PORT ELIZABETH - Convicted murderer Christopher Panayiotou will be sentenced on Friday. Panayiotou masterminded the murder of his wife, Jayde Panayiotou, two years ago. Jayde was shot dead after she was kidnapped outside her home in Port Elizabeth. Her body was found in a veld just outside Uitenhage a day later. READ: Panayiotou sentencing postponed Accomplice Sinethemba Nenembe was convicted on a charge of murder and robbery. Zolani Sibeko was found guilty of conspiracy to commit murder. The alleged shooter, Sizwezakhe Vumazonke, died while awaiting trial. During the trial a video recording in which Christopher Panayiotou appeared to implicate himself in his wife’s murder, was viewed in court. Panayiotou’s mistress, Chanelle Coutts, testified that she received expensive gifts from the accused.  !function(d,s,id){var js,fjs=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0],p=/^http:/.test(d.location)?'http':'https';if(!d.getElementById(id)){js=d.createElement(s);js.id=id;js.src=p+"://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js";fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);}}(document,"script","twitter-wjs"); eNCA